{
  "text": "where D V is the vessel diameter as measured in eqn (3). The ultrastructure of intervessel pits was observed using a field emission scanning electron microscope (Jeol JSM-7600F, Tokyo, Japan) and a JEOL JEM 1400-Plus transmission electron microscope (JEOL, Tokyo, Japan), as described in [CITATION_1] . Since we observed intervessel pit membranes from the central stem segment parts where centrifugal force was applied, our measurements provide a relative estimation of intervessel pit membrane thickness.",
